shutdown_situation
Disk World creator help
shutdown_situation

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
shutdown_situation -  Shuts down a situation or set of situations initiated with change_situation based on the call_out handle returned by the call to change_situation.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void shutdown_situation(int call,
mixed label)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^callout%^RESET%^ - call_out handle.  If 0 then the last
known handle is used.
%^BOLD%^label%^RESET%^ - label or array of labels of situations to clean 
up with end_situation
%^BOLD%^the_room%^RESET%^ - the room
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/room/basic_room.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

Shuts down a situation or set of situations initiated with
change_situation based on the call_out handle
returned by the call to change_situation.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
automate_situation, change_situation

.EP

